{
  "stem": "9262.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we didn't have much, but we couldn't see anyone, in winter, being without socks, or torn trousers, or even overcoats.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So whatever we had, we gave it to them, some of the children.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] Some people-- some Jewish people, who had jobs or they owned business, were all right.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Some looked after their families, others sort of didn't bother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "They were very, very selfish.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Now, my father's family was very, very clannish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "They looked after each other, and I think this was really a blessing that, when we came, we had a home to go to, we had people who cared after us, people who took an interest in us.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And that was really very good.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The non-Jewish population was very antisemitic.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I would say, and that is, in all fairness, without any prejudice, that the Polish antisemitism was much stronger before the war than what we experienced in Germany.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It manifested itself that [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] they hated Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When you went into an official [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] office of the government, like a tax office-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] a large population of Jews were Hasidic, and they always wore their skull cap.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They would take off their hat, or their cap, and they would still have the skull cap covering their head.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when the Poles saw that, they used to go to them and they used to have kind of [? tantrums. ?] They used to knock them on the head and they said, oi, Jew man, this is a government office.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Respect for the government.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Take your hat off.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they knew that these Jewish people would never really take their hat off.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But there was no alternative, and they took it off.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
